---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="The Mectov Linux philosophy. Learn why we build an optimized, brutalist, and speed-centric Arch-based distribution.">
  <div class="container about-container">
    
    <header class="about-header">
      <h1 class="about-title">SYSTEM_MANIFESTO</h1>
      <p class="about-subtitle">> Our core philosophy. Raw power. Absolute control.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-layout">
      <!-- Left Column: Manifesto & Philosophy -->
      <section class="manifesto-content">
        <h2 class="section-heading">// WHY MECTOV?</h2>
        <p class="manifesto-p">
          Most modern operating systems are bloated. They compile their binaries for the lowest common denominator, wasting the hardware capability sitting right on your desk. They bundle cloud integration, background AI agents, and telemetry that spy on your keystrokes.
        </p>
        <p class="manifesto-p">
          <strong>Mectov Linux</strong> is built by developers, for developers who reject the status quo. It is a raw, fast, and uncompromised operating system. We take the flexibility of Arch Linux and combine it with the aggressive compiling optimizations of CachyOS to squeeze every clock cycle from your silicon.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-heading">// CORE PILARS</h2>
        
        <div class="pillar-box">
          <h3 class="pillar-title">1. COMPILER LEVEL SPEED</h3>
          <p class="pillar-text">
            We don't distribute generic x86-64 binaries. Mectov repositories compile packages specifically targeting <strong>x86-64-v3</strong> and <strong>x86-64-v4</strong> instructions (AVX2, AVX-512, FMA3). This delivers an instant 10-25% performance improvement in heavy computational workloads, directly out of the box.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar-box">
          <h3 class="pillar-title">2. BURST-ORIENTED SCHEDULING</h3>
          <p class="pillar-text">
            Powered by the custom <strong>BORE (Burst-Oriented Response Enhancer)</strong> CPU scheduler. Rather than balancing threads evenly, BORE detects user-interactive software and schedules processor cores instantly to avoid cursor lag, audio clipping, or desktop stuttering under extreme compilations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar-box">
          <h3 class="pillar-title">3. ANARCHY BASE</h3>
          <p class="pillar-text">
            Built on the Arch Linux rolling release model. You get the newest packages within hours of upstream release. No scheduled updates, no forced reboots. You upgrade when you command, not when the OS decides.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Right Column: Specs Panel -->
      <aside class="specs-panel">
        <div class="terminal-card">
          <div class="terminal-card-header">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span class="title">build-specifications.conf</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-card-body">
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">TARGET_ARCH</span>="x86_64-v3, x86_64-v4"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">COMPILER</span>="GCC 14.1.1 + LLVM Clang 18"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">CFLAGS</span>="-march=native -O3 -flto=auto -pipe"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">LDFLAGS</span>="-Wl,-O1,--sort-common,--as-needed,-z,relro,-z,now"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">BASE_DISTRO</span>="Arch Linux Baseline"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">REPO_MIRRORS</span>="CachyOS Pacman Repositories"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">SCHEDULER</span>="EEVDF-BORE (Burst Enhancer)"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">INIT_SYSTEM</span>="systemd rolling-release"</p>
            <p class="code-line"><span class="cyan">DEFAULT_SHELL</span>="Zsh + OhMyZsh config"</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="manifesto-badge">
          <div class="badge-accent-bar"></div>
          <p class="badge-text">
            "We build systems that feel like tools, not products. If it is too neat, it isn't Mectov."
          </p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.about-container {
  padding-top: 3rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2rem;
}

.about-header {
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--text-primary);
  padding-bottom: 1rem;
}

.about-title {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  color: var(--accent-cyan);
}

.about-subtitle {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  color: var(--text-muted);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}

.about-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
  gap: 3rem;
  align-items: start;
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .about-layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }
}

.section-heading {
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--accent-cyan);
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.section-heading:first-of-type {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.manifesto-p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

/* Pillar container styling */
.pillar-box {
  border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-red);
  padding-left: 1.25rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.pillar-title {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.pillar-text {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.5;
}

/* Specs Terminal Card styling */
.terminal-card {
  background-color: #000;
  border: 4px solid var(--text-primary);
  box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--accent-cyan);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.terminal-card-header {
  background-color: var(--text-primary);
  color: var(--bg-color);
  padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}

.terminal-card-header .dot {
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
  background-color: var(--accent-red);
  display: inline-block;
}

.terminal-card-body {
  padding: 1.25rem;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  overflow-x: auto;
}

.code-line {
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.code-line:last-of-type {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.code-line .cyan {
  color: var(--accent-cyan);
  font-weight: bold;
}

/* Accent Quote Badge */
.manifesto-badge {
  border: 2px solid var(--text-muted);
  padding: 1.5rem;
  position: relative;
  background-color: rgba(255, 42, 75, 0.02);
}

.badge-accent-bar {
  position: absolute;
  top: -2px;
  left: 10%;
  width: 40px;
  height: 4px;
  background-color: var(--accent-red);
}

.badge-text {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--accent-red);
  line-height: 1.4;
  margin: 0;
}
</style>
